<darkcolour>A6416E</darkcolour><section><title>Past Simple Passive</title><sectiontitle>When we say what people and things do, we use active verb forms, for example &lt;I&gt;gave, took&lt;/I&gt; and &lt;I&gt;made&lt;/I&gt;.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Pre-intGRAM_9_3_1.mp3</titlesound><text1></text1><sound1>Pre-intGRAM_9_3_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>Charles &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;stole&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; her bag.</text1a><text2></text2><sound2>Pre-intGRAM_9_3_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>Sarah &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;took&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; a beautiful photo.</text2a><titlesound2>Pre-intGRAM_9_3_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>When we say what happens to things or people or what is done to them we often use passive verb forms, for example &lt;I&gt;was given, were taken&lt;/I&gt; and &lt;I&gt;was made&lt;/I&gt;.</sectiontitle2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>Pre-intGRAM_9_3_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>Her bag&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt; was stolen.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>Pre-intGRAM_9_3_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>The camera &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;was made&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; in China.</text4a></section><section><title>Past Simple Passive</title><sectiontitle>We often use the passive when the person or thing (the agent) is unknown or not important. The form of the Past Simple Passive is &lt;I&gt;was/were&lt;/I&gt; + past participle.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Pre-intGRAM_9_3_7.mp3</titlesound><text1></text1><sound1>Pre-intGRAM_9_3_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>This house &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;was built&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; in 1745.</text1a><text2></text2><sound2>Pre-intGRAM_9_3_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>We &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;weren't given&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; anything to eat.</text2a><titlesound2>%undefined</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>%undefined</sectiontitle2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>%undefined</sound3><text3a>%undefined</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>%undefined</sound4><text4a>%undefined</text4a></section></grammar>